findSheet.docstring:
Find a worksheet by name (case-insensitive), returning null if not found.
Non-throwing alternative to {@link getSheet}.
@param - Sheet name (case-insensitive)
@returns The worksheet, or null if no sheet with that name exists

getOrCreateSheet.docstring:
Get a sheet by name, creating it if it doesn't exist.
@param - Sheet name (case-insensitive lookup)
@returns The sheet and whether it was newly created

captureScreenshot.docstring:
Capture a PNG screenshot of a cell range.
@param - Sheet name (e.g. "Sheet1") or Worksheet instance
@param - A1-notation cell range (e.g. "A1:G10")
@param - Rendering options (DPR, headers, gridlines, max dimensions)
@returns PNG image as a Buffer

[Symbol.asyncDispose].docstring:
Async dispose for TC39 Explicit Resource Management.
@example ```typescript
await using wb = await createWorkbook();
```

history.goToIndex.docstring:
Undo to a specific index in the history.
Performs multiple undo operations to reach the target state.
@param - Index in the history (0 = most recent operation)

history.subscribe.docstring:
Subscribe to undo/redo state changes.
Called whenever the undo stack changes (push, undo, redo, clear).
@returns Unsubscribe function

names.add.docstring:
Define a new named range.
@param - The name to define.
@param - A1-style reference (e.g. "Sheet1!$A$1:$B$10"). May omit leading "=".
@param - Optional descriptive comment.
@param - Optional sheet name scope. Omit for workbook-scoped names.

names.has.docstring:
Check if a named range exists.
@param - The name to check.
@param - Optional sheet name scope. Omit for workbook-scoped names.
@returns True if the named range exists.

names.get.docstring:
Get a named range by name.
@param - The name to look up.
@param - Optional sheet name scope. Omit for workbook-scoped names.
@returns The named range info, or null if not found.

names.getRange.docstring:
Get the parsed sheet reference for a named range.
Returns the sheet name and range portion for names that refer to a simple
sheet!range reference. Returns null if the name is not found or if the
reference is not a simple sheet!range format (e.g., a formula).
@param - The name to look up.
@param - Optional sheet name scope. Omit for workbook-scoped names.
@returns The parsed reference, or null if not found or not a simple range.

names.remove.docstring:
Remove a named range.
@param - The name to remove.
@param - Optional sheet name scope. Omit for workbook-scoped names.

names.update.docstring:
Update an existing named range.
@param - The current name to update.
@param - Fields to change (name, reference, comment).
@param - Optional sheet name scope. Omit for workbook-scoped names.

names.createFromSelection.docstring:
Create named ranges from row/column labels in a selection.
Scans edges of the selection for label text and creates names referring to
the corresponding data cells.
@param - Sheet containing the selection (name or SheetId).
@param - The cell range to scan for labels.
@param - Which edges to scan (top, left, bottom, right).
@returns Counts of successfully created and skipped names.

names.getValue.docstring:
Get the computed value of a named item as a display-formatted string.
For single-cell references, returns the formatted cell value.
For range references, returns the raw A1 reference string.
@param - The named item to evaluate.
@param - Optional sheet name scope for resolution precedence.
@returns The display value, or null if the name doesn't exist.

names.getType.docstring:
Get the API type of a named item's resolved value.
@param - The named item to inspect.
@param - Optional sheet name scope for resolution precedence.
@returns The type string, or null if the name doesn't exist.

names.getArrayValues.docstring:
Get the 2D array of resolved values for a named range.
For single-cell references, returns a 1×1 array.
For multi-cell ranges, returns the full grid.
@param - The named item to evaluate.
@param - Optional sheet name scope for resolution precedence.
@returns The 2D value array, or null if the name doesn't exist or isn't a range.

names.getArrayTypes.docstring:
Get the 2D array of type classifications for each cell in a named range.
@param - The named item to evaluate.
@param - Optional sheet name scope for resolution precedence.
@returns The 2D type array, or null if the name doesn't exist or isn't a range.

names.getValueAsJson.docstring:
Get the raw typed value of a named item as a JSON-compatible value.
For single-cell references, returns the cell's typed value (string, number, boolean, null, or error).
For range references, returns the first cell's value.
For constants, returns the constant as a string.
@param - The named item to evaluate.
@param - Optional sheet name scope for resolution precedence.
@returns The typed value, or null if the name doesn't exist.

names.recalculateDependents.docstring:
Recalculate all formulas that depend on a given named range.
Called after a name is created, updated, or deleted so that
dependent cells reflect the new definition (or show #NAME? errors).
@param - The name that changed (case-insensitive).
@param - Current active sheet for relative reference resolution.
@param - Transaction origin (default: 'user').

scenarios.add.docstring:
Add a what-if scenario.
@param - Scenario configuration (name, changing cells, values).
@returns The newly created scenario's ID.

scenarios.apply.docstring:
Apply a scenario's values to the worksheet.
@param - The scenario ID to apply.
@returns Result including cells updated count and original values for restore.

scenarios.update.docstring:
Update an existing scenario's configuration.
@param - The scenario ID to update.
@param - Partial configuration with fields to change.

sheets.add.docstring:
Add a new sheet to the workbook.
@param - Optional sheet name. Defaults to "SheetN".
@param - Optional 0-based position to insert the sheet.
@returns The created Worksheet.

sheets.remove.docstring:
Remove a sheet by index or name.
Throws if attempting to remove the last sheet.
@param - 0-based index or sheet name.

sheets.move.docstring:
Move a sheet to a new position.
@param - 0-based index or sheet name to move.
@param - Target 0-based index.

sheets.rename.docstring:
Rename a sheet.
@param - 0-based index or current sheet name.
@param - The new name for the sheet.

sheets.copy.docstring:
Copy a sheet within the workbook.
@param - 0-based index or name of the sheet to copy.
@param - Optional name for the copy. Defaults to "SheetName (Copy)".
@param - Optional 0-based position for the copy.
@returns The newly created Worksheet.

sheets.hide.docstring:
Hide a sheet.
Throws if attempting to hide the last visible sheet.
@param - 0-based index or sheet name.

sheets.on.docstring:
Subscribe to sheet collection events.
Fires for: sheetAdded, sheetRemoved, sheetRenamed, activeSheetChanged.
@param - Event type
@param - Event handler receiving the typed internal event
@returns CallableDisposable — call directly or `.dispose()` to unsubscribe

slicers.get.docstring:
Get a slicer by ID from any sheet.
@param - ID of the slicer
@returns Full slicer state, or null if not found

slicers.getItemAt.docstring:
Get a slicer by its zero-based index in the list.
@param - Zero-based index of the slicer
@returns Slicer summary information, or null if index is out of range

slicers.getItems.docstring:
Get the items (values) available in a slicer by ID.
@param - ID of the slicer
@returns Array of slicer items with selection state

slicers.getItem.docstring:
Get a slicer item by its string key.
@param - ID of the slicer
@param - The value to look up (matched via string coercion)
@returns The matching slicer item
@throws KernelError if no item matches the key

slicers.getItemOrNullObject.docstring:
Get a slicer item by its string key, or null if not found.
@param - ID of the slicer
@param - The value to look up (matched via string coercion)
@returns The matching slicer item, or null if not found

getRanges.docstring:
Get cell data for multiple ranges at once (spreadsheet special-cell typeWorksheet.getRanges equivalent).
@param - Comma-separated A1-style range addresses (e.g. "A1:B5,D1:E5,G1")
@returns Array of 2D cell data arrays, one per address

clear.docstring:
Unified clear with mode selection (spreadsheet special-cell typeRange.clear equivalent).
@param - A1 range string (e.g. "A1:C3")
@param - What to clear: 'all' (default), 'contents', 'formats', 'hyperlinks'

getValues.docstring:
Get cell values for a range as a 2D array. Returns primitive values only
(no formatting, formulas, or metadata). Empty cells are null.

This is the most common read pattern for SDK/LLM consumers.
@param - A1-style range string (e.g. "A1:C10")
@returns 2D array of cell values

evaluate.docstring:
Evaluate a formula expression in the context of this sheet without writing
it to any cell. The expression should not include the leading `=`.
@example const total = await ws.evaluate("SUM(A1:A10)");
@param - Formula expression string (e.g. "SUM(A1:A10)")
@returns The computed result value

getFormulaArray.docstring:
Get the array formula for a cell that is part of a dynamic array spill.

If the cell is the source of a dynamic array (e.g., =SEQUENCE(5)), returns
the formula. If the cell is a spill member (projected from a source), returns
the source cell's formula. Returns null if the cell is not part of an array.
@param - A1-style cell address
@returns The array formula string, or null if not an array cell

findInRange.docstring:
Find the first cell matching text within a range (spreadsheet special-cell typeRange.find equivalent).
@param - A1 range string to search within
@param - Text or regex pattern to search for
@param - Search options (matchCase, entireCell)
@returns The first matching SearchResult, or null if no match found

replaceAll.docstring:
Find and replace all occurrences within a range (spreadsheet special-cell typeRange.replaceAll equivalent).
@param - A1 range string to search within
@param - Text to find
@param - Replacement text
@param - Search options (matchCase, entireCell)
@returns Number of replacements made

getExtendedRange.docstring:
Get the extended range in a direction (spreadsheet special-cell typeRange.getExtendedRange / Ctrl+Shift+Arrow).

From the active cell (default: top-left of range), finds the data edge in the given
direction and returns a range extending from the original range to that edge.
@param - A1 range string (current selection)
@param - Direction to extend
@param - Optional active cell override (default: top-left of range)
@returns Extended range as a worksheet-scoped public range

isEntireColumn.docstring:
Check if a range represents entire column(s) (e.g., "A:C").
@param - A1 range string or CellRange object
@returns True if the range represents entire column(s)

isEntireRow.docstring:
Check if a range represents entire row(s) (e.g., "1:5").
@param - A1 range string or CellRange object
@returns True if the range represents entire row(s)

getVisibleView.docstring:
Get only the visible (non-hidden) rows from a range (visible range-view equivalent).

Filters out rows hidden by AutoFilter or manual hide operations.
Returns cell values for visible rows only, along with the absolute row indices.
@param - A1 range string (e.g., "A1:Z100")
@returns Visible rows' values and their indices

getSpecialCells.docstring:
Find cells matching a special cell type (spreadsheet special-cell typeRange.getSpecialCells equivalent).

Returns addresses of cells matching the specified type within the used range.
Optionally filter by value type when cellType is `Constants` or `Formulas`.
@param - The type of cells to find
@param - Optional value type filter (only for Constants/Formulas)
@returns Array of matching cell addresses

getValueForEditing.docstring:
Get the edit-mode string representation of a cell value.
Used by formula bar and in-cell editing.

For formula cells, returns the formula string (e.g. "=SUM(A1:A10)").
For date/time cells, returns pre-computed edit text if available.
For value cells, returns the raw value as a string.
@param - Row index (0-based)
@param - Column index (0-based)
@param - Optional pre-computed edit text (for date/time cells)
@returns The string to display in edit mode

getDisplayValues.docstring:
Get the formatted display values for a range as a 2D array.

Returns the same formatted strings shown in each cell (number formats applied,
dates formatted, etc.). This is the range counterpart to `getDisplayValue()`.
@param - A1-style range string (e.g. "A1:C10")
@returns 2D array of formatted display strings

getValueTypes.docstring:
Get per-cell value type classification for a range (spreadsheet special-cell typeRange.valueTypes equivalent).
@param - A1 range string or CellRange object
@returns 2D array of RangeValueType enums

getNumberFormatCategories.docstring:
Get per-cell number format category for a range (spreadsheet special-cell typeRange.numberFormatCategories equivalent).
@param - A1 range string or CellRange object
@returns 2D array of NumberFormatCategory enums

sortByColor.docstring:
Sort a range by cell or font color, putting matched-color rows on top or bottom.

Convenience wrapper over {@link sortRange} with a single color-keyed criterion.
Excel/ECMA-376 vocabulary: `'fill'` is the cell background fill, `'font'` is
the cell font color. Compares the resolved per-cell effective format.
@param - A1-style range string or CellRange object
@param - Color sort options (column, color type, target color, top/bottom position)

moveTo.docstring:
Move (relocate) cells from a source range to a target position.

Moves cell values, formulas, and formatting. Formula references within the
moved range are adjusted to the new position. The source range is cleared
after the move.
@param - Source range in A1 notation (e.g., "A1:B10")
@param - Destination top-left row (0-based)
@param - Destination top-left column (0-based)

copyFrom.docstring:
Copy cells from a source range to a target range with optional paste-special behavior.

Supports selective copy (values only, formulas only, formats only, or all),
skip-blanks, and transpose. Maps to spreadsheet special-cell typeRange.copyFrom().
@param - Source range in A1 notation (e.g., "A1:B10")
@param - Target range in A1 notation (e.g., "D1:E10")
@param - Optional paste-special behavior (copyType, skipBlanks, transpose)

setListValidation.docstring:
Set list validation on a cell or range.

Shortcut for `ws.validations.setList(range, source, options)`.
@param - A1-style cell/range address or CellRange object
@param - Inline values, inline CSV, A1 source range, formula/named source, or CellRange
@param - Optional validation UI and enforcement metadata

setFormulaConditionalFormat.docstring:
Add a formula-based conditional format for a cell or range.

Shortcut for `ws.conditionalFormats.addFormula(range, formula, style)`.
@param - A1-style cell/range address, CellRange object, or array of ranges
@param - Conditional-format formula (e.g. "=A1>100")
@param - Style applied when the formula is true

bindings.get.docstring:
Get a data binding by ID.
@param - The binding ID to retrieve
@returns The binding info, or null if not found

bindings.add.docstring:
Add a new data binding on the sheet.
@param - Binding configuration (connection, column mappings, etc.)
@returns The created binding info

bindings.getProjectionRange.docstring:
Get the spill range for a projected (dynamic array) cell.
@param - Row index (0-based)
@param - Column index (0-based)
@returns The spill range, or null if the cell is not a projection source

bindings.getProjectionSource.docstring:
Get the source cell of a projected value.
@param - Row index (0-based)
@param - Column index (0-based)
@returns The source cell position, or null if the cell is not a projection

bindings.isProjectedPosition.docstring:
Check whether a cell position is a projected (spilled) value.
@param - Row index (0-based)
@param - Column index (0-based)
@returns True if the cell holds a projected value

bindings.getViewportProjectionData.docstring:
Get all projection data overlapping a viewport range (batch query).
Returns one entry per projection with origin position and dimensions.
@param - A1-style range string or CellRange object

comments.addNote.docstring:
Add a note to a cell (options object form).
@param - A1-style cell address (e.g. "A1")
@param - Note text and optional author

comments.setNote.docstring:
@deprecated Use the options-object overload instead.
Set the note for a cell (overwrites any existing note).
@param - A1-style cell address (e.g. "A1")
@param - Note text
@param - Optional author name (defaults to 'api')
@deprecated Use the options-object overload instead.

comments.getNote.docstring:
Get the note for a cell as a Note object.
@param - A1-style cell address
@returns The Note object, or null if no note

comments.getNoteAt.docstring:
Get a note by index from the list of all notes.
@param - Zero-based index into the notes list
@returns The Note at that index, or null if out of range

comments.setNoteVisible.docstring:
Set the visibility of a note at the given cell address.
@param - A1-style cell address
@param - Whether the note should be visible

comments.setNoteHeight.docstring:
Set the height of a note callout box in points.
@param - A1-style cell address
@param - Height in points

comments.setNoteWidth.docstring:
Set the width of a note callout box in points.
@param - A1-style cell address
@param - Width in points

comments.add.docstring:
Add a threaded comment to a cell (options object form).
@param - A1-style cell address
@param - Comment text and optional author

comments.update.docstring:
Update an existing comment.
@param - Comment identifier
@param - Object with fields to update (text, mentions, or both)

comments.resolveThread.docstring:
Set the resolved state of a comment thread.
@param - Thread identifier (cell ID)
@param - Whether the thread should be marked as resolved

comments.getForCell.docstring:
Get all comments for a specific cell.
@param - A1-style cell address
@returns Array of comments for the cell

comments.addReply.docstring:
Add a reply to an existing comment.
@param - ID of the comment to reply to
@param - Reply text
@param - Author name or identifier
@returns Receipt containing the created reply comment

comments.convertNoteToThread.docstring:
Convert a legacy note into a modern threaded comment.

Flips `commentType` to `'threadedComment'`, clears note callout geometry
(`noteHeight`/`noteWidth`/`visible`/`shapeId`), and assigns `threadId`.
Idempotent on a comment that is already a threaded comment.
@param - ID of the note to convert
@returns Receipt containing the updated comment so the caller can re-render in thread mode

comments.getThread.docstring:
Get all comments in a thread (root + replies), sorted by createdAt.
@param - ID of any comment in the thread
@returns Array of comments in the thread

comments.getById.docstring:
Get a single comment by its ID.
@param - Comment identifier
@returns The comment, or null if not found

comments.getLocation.docstring:
Get the A1-style cell address for a comment.

Resolves the comment's internal cell reference (CellId) to a
human-readable address like "A1", "B3", etc.
@param - Comment identifier
@returns The A1-style cell address, or null if the comment doesn't exist

comments.getParentByReplyId.docstring:
Get the parent comment for a reply.
@param - ID of the reply comment
@returns The parent comment, or null if not found or not a reply

comments.getReplyCount.docstring:
Get the number of replies in a thread (excluding the root comment).
@param - ID of any comment in the thread
@returns The reply count

comments.getReplyAt.docstring:
Get a reply at a specific index within a thread (zero-based, excludes root).
@param - ID of any comment in the thread
@param - Zero-based index into the replies
@returns The reply comment, or null if out of range

comments.getNoteLocation.docstring:
Get the A1-style cell address for a note.
@param - A1-style cell address
@returns The A1-style cell address, or null if no note exists at that address

comments.hasComment.docstring:
Check if a cell has any comments.
@param - A1-style cell address
@returns True if the cell has at least one comment

comments.removeForCell.docstring:
Remove all comments on a cell.
@param - A1-style cell address
@returns Number of comments removed

conditionalFormats.addFormula.docstring:
Add a formula-based conditional format for a range.

This is the intent-level wrapper for the common case. It creates a single
formula rule and assigns IDs/priorities through the same path as {@link add}.
Formula strings may include the leading `=` or omit it.
@param - Cell range, or array of ranges, this format applies to
@param - Conditional-format formula (e.g. "=A1>100")
@param - Style applied when the formula is true
@returns Receipt with the created conditional format, assigned IDs, and affected ranges

conditionalFormats.add.docstring:
Add a new conditional format with ranges and rules.
The API assigns IDs and priorities — callers provide rule configuration only.
@param - Cell ranges this format applies to
@param - Rule inputs (without id/priority)
@returns Receipt with the created conditional format, assigned IDs, and affected ranges

conditionalFormats.get.docstring:
Get a conditional format by its ID.
@param - Format ID to look up
@returns The conditional format, or null if not found

conditionalFormats.has.docstring:
Check if a conditional format exists by ID.
@param - Format ID to check
@returns True if the format exists

conditionalFormats.update.docstring:
Update an existing conditional format.
Supports replacing rules, ranges, and setting stopIfTrue on all rules.
@param - Format ID to update
@param - Object with optional rules, ranges, and stopIfTrue

conditionalFormats.clearRuleStyle.docstring:
Clear the style of a specific rule within a conditional format, resetting
all style properties (font, fill, border, number format) to unset.
@param - Format ID containing the rule
@param - Rule ID within the format to clear style for

conditionalFormats.changeRuleType.docstring:
Change the type and configuration of a specific rule within a conditional format,
preserving its ID and priority. This is the equivalent of eight
changeRuleTo*() methods, unified into one type-safe call using CFRuleInput.
@param - Format ID containing the rule
@param - Rule ID to change
@param - New rule configuration (type + type-specific fields)

conditionalFormats.getItemAt.docstring:
Get a conditional format by its index in the priority-ordered list.
@param - Zero-based index
@returns The conditional format at that index, or null if out of bounds

conditionalFormats.removeRule.docstring:
Remove a single rule from a conditional format. If the removed rule was
the last rule in the format, the conditional format itself is removed.
@param - Format ID containing the rule
@param - Rule ID to remove

conditionalFormats.cloneForPaste.docstring:
Clone conditional formats from source to target with offset.
Used by format painter and paste operations.
@param - Source sheet ID (for cut operation reference removal)
@param - Relative CF formats with range offsets
@param - Target paste origin (row, col)
@param - Whether this is a cut operation

filters.byColor.docstring:
Filter a column by cell or font color.

Convenience wrapper over {@link setColumnFilter} with a color predicate —
rows whose column-`col` cell does not match the requested color are hidden.

When `opts.filterId` is omitted, targets the first auto-filter on the sheet.
@param - Column index (0-based, absolute)
@param - Color filter options

filters.setAutoFilter.docstring:
@deprecated Use {@link add} instead.
Set an auto-filter on the sheet by parsing an A1-style range string.
@param - A1-style range string (e.g. "A1:D100")

filters.clearAutoFilter.docstring:
@deprecated Use {@link clear} instead.
Clear the auto-filter from the sheet.
Removes all filters, not just criteria.

filters.getAutoFilter.docstring:
@deprecated Use {@link get} instead.
Get the current auto-filter state.
@returns The filter state, or null if no auto-filter is set

filters.getForRange.docstring:
Get the filter overlapping a range, or null if none.
@param - A1-style range string (e.g. "A1:D100")
@returns Object with filter ID if found, or null

filters.setColumnFilter.docstring:
Set filter criteria for a column on an auto-filter.

When `filterId` is omitted, targets the first auto-filter (convenience shorthand).
When provided, targets the specified filter directly.
@param - Column index (0-based)
@param - Filter criteria to apply
@param - Optional filter ID; defaults to first auto-filter

filters.applyDynamicFilter.docstring:
Apply a dynamic filter rule to a column on an auto-filter.

Dynamic filters are pre-defined rules resolved against live data,
such as "above average", "below average", or date-relative rules
like "today", "this month", etc.

When `filterId` is omitted, targets the first auto-filter.
@param - Column index (0-based)
@param - Dynamic filter rule to apply
@param - Optional filter ID; defaults to first auto-filter

filters.clearColumnFilter.docstring:
Clear filter criteria for a column on an auto-filter.

When `filterId` is omitted, targets the first auto-filter.
When provided, targets the specified filter directly.
@param - Column index (0-based)
@param - Optional filter ID; defaults to first auto-filter

filters.getUniqueValues.docstring:
Get unique values in a column (for filter dropdowns).

When `filterId` is omitted, uses the first auto-filter.
@param - Column index (0-based)
@param - Optional filter ID; defaults to first auto-filter
@returns Array of unique values

filters.getFilterDropdownData.docstring:
Get complete value-list dropdown data for a filter column.

Returns nonblank items plus first-class blank metadata from the same
table/filter engine path used to apply value filters.
@param - Column index (0-based, absolute)
@param - Optional filter ID; defaults to first auto-filter

filters.setCriteria.docstring:
@deprecated Use {@link setColumnFilter} instead.
Set filter criteria for a column on a specific filter by ID (advanced).
@param - Filter ID
@param - Column index (0-based)
@param - Filter criteria to apply

filters.clearCriteria.docstring:
@deprecated Use {@link clearColumnFilter} instead.
Clear filter criteria for a column on a specific filter by ID (advanced).
@param - Filter ID
@param - Column index (0-based)

filters.clearAllCriteria.docstring:
Clear all filter criteria for a filter.
Removes filters from all columns but keeps the filter structure intact.
@param - Filter ID

filters.getInfo.docstring:
Get detailed filter info including resolved range and column filters.
@param - Filter ID
@returns Detailed filter info, or null if not found

filters.getFilterUniqueValues.docstring:
@deprecated Use {@link getUniqueValues} instead.
Get unique values for a filter column.
@param - Filter ID
@param - Column index (0-based)
@returns Array of unique values

filters.list.docstring:
List all filters in the sheet with full detail (resolved numeric ranges
and converted column-filter criteria).
@returns Array of detailed filter info objects

filters.getSortState.docstring:
Get the sort state for a filter.
@param - Filter ID
@returns Sort state, or null if no sort state set

filters.setSortState.docstring:
Set the sort state for a filter.
@param - Filter ID
@param - Sort state to set

formats.set.docstring:
Set format for a single cell.
@param - A1-style cell address (e.g. "A1", "B3")
@param - Format properties to apply
@example // Bold red currency
await ws.formats.set('A1', { bold: true, fontColor: '#ff0000', numberFormat: '$#,##0.00' });
// Date format
await ws.formats.set('B1', { numberFormat: 'YYYY-MM-DD' });
// Header style
await ws.formats.set('A1', { bold: true, fontSize: 14, backgroundColor: '#4472c4', fontColor: '#ffffff' });

formats.setRange.docstring:
Set format for a contiguous range.
@param - A1-style range string (e.g. "A1:B2")
@param - Format properties to apply
@example // Currency column
await ws.formats.setRange('B2:B100', { numberFormat: '$#,##0.00' });
// Header row with borders
await ws.formats.setRange('A1:F1', {
  bold: true,
  backgroundColor: '#4472c4',
  fontColor: '#ffffff',
  borders: { bottom: { style: 'medium', color: '#2f5496' } }
});

formats.setRanges.docstring:
